== New Sequel ==

The events of both ''[[Alien 3]]'' and ''[[Alien: Resurrection]]'' will be ignored by the upcoming sequel to ''[[Aliens (film)|Aliens]]'', which will be directed by [[Neill Blomkamp]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/02/26/neill-blomkamp-alien-sequel_n_6759418.html|title=Neill Blomkamp's 'Alien' Sequel Will Probably Forget About Two 'Alien' Movies|last=Rosen|first=Christopher|work=The Huffington Post|date=February 26, 2015|accessdate=February 26, 2015}}</ref> [[User:AdamDeanHall|AdamDeanHall]] ([[User talk:AdamDeanHall|talk]]) 23:37, 26 February 2015 (UTC)

Note - 
[http://variety.com/2015/film/news/new-alien-wont-undo-alien-3%E2%80%B2-or-resurrection-director-neill-blomkamp-says-1201443899/ Variety: New ‘Alien’ Won’t Undo ‘Alien 3′ or ‘Resurrection,’ Director Neill Blomkamp Says] - [[User:Gothicfilm|Gothicfilm]] ([[User talk:Gothicfilm|talk]]) 22:34, 1 March 2015 (UTC)
{{reflist-talk}}
==Production country==
Just as a heads up. I added a possibly mildly controversial addition for the production country. In the [[Monthly Film Bulletin]], the film is listed as simply a British production, noting that the 20th-Century Fox production is from a London division. I've changed the article to reflect this and added the source. [[User:Andrzejbanas|Andrzejbanas]] ([[User talk:Andrzejbanas|talk]]) 12:42, 25 August 2015 (UTC)
:On returning, I've noticed someone removed cited material and added some bare-url google searches. Let's try to come to a conclusion before just removing material we don't agree with. [[User:Andrzejbanas|Andrzejbanas]] ([[User talk:Andrzejbanas|talk]]) 17:35, 12 October 2015 (UTC)
:With a little research, I found this snippet of information from the ever useful [[British Film Institute]], stating the film was "[http://www.bfi.org.uk/news-opinion/news-bfi/lists/10-great-british-sci-fi-films American funded, but made by Twentieth Century-Fox’s British production subsidiary]". Not sure how much that helps. [[User:Andrzejbanas|Andrzejbanas]] ([[User talk:Andrzejbanas|talk]]) 17:37, 12 October 2015 (UTC)
:As a heads up here as well, the Academy Awards seems to note the British production status here: [http://awardsdatabase.oscars.org/ampas_awards/DisplayMain.jsp?curTime=1444820564759]. [[User:Andrzejbanas|Andrzejbanas]] ([[User talk:Andrzejbanas|talk]]) 01:05, 15 October 2015 (UTC)

